The '''''British Central Africa Gazette''''' was the [[government gazette]] of the [[British Central Africa Protectorate]].
The ''Gazette'' was published monthly at Milia between 1894 and September 1907<ref>[http://www.crl.edu/collections/topics/official-gazettes/search?titleID=t72&pc=1 BRITISH CENTRAL AFRICA PROTECTORATE] CRL Foreign Official Gazette Database, 2014. Retrieved 28 May 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/6PtZ3H80D?url=http://www.crl.edu/collections/topics/official-gazettes/search?titleID%3Dt72%26pc%3D1 Archived here.]</ref> in English. Copies may be found in the collections of the [[British Library]]<ref>[http://www.bl.uk/reshelp/findhelpregion/africa/malawi/acmalawi/ Malawi official publications] British Library, 2014. Retrieved 28 May 2014.</ref> and the Library of Congress.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.loc.gov/item/sn89049469/|title=The British Central Africa gazette.|work=The Library of Congress|access-date=2018-08-18|language=en}}</ref> It was replaced by the ''[[Nyasaland Government Gazette|Nyasaland government gazette]] in October 1907.''
