==Commentators and spokespersons== *Commentators - [[Gábor Gundel Takács]]<ref name="Hungarian">{{cite web|url=http://eschungary.hu/news/2008/belgrad2008_mtv_musor.html|title=Information on Hungarian broadcasting|publisher=eschungary.extra.hu|accessdate=2008-05-06|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080510094342/http://eschungary.hu/news/2008/belgrad2008_mtv_musor.html|archivedate=2008-05-10|df=}}</ref> *Spokespersons - [[Éva Novodomszky]]<ref name="Hungarian"/>
==At Eurovision== In previous years, if a country placed in the top 10 countries in the final they automatically qualified to the final of the next contest. Had this rule remained for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008 contest]], Hungary would have directly qualified for the final. However, a change in rules due to the large intake of countries participating in the contest meant that only five countries, the host country and the [[Eurovision Song Contest#Big 4|Big 4]] countries, would automatically qualify to the final. As such, Hungary were forced to compete in one of the two semi-finals of the 2008 contest in [[Serbia]]. She competed in the second semi-final on May 22, performing fifteenth. She placed nineteenth and last with six points, getting four points from [[Serbia]], one from [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] and one from [[Denmark]].
