The '''International Federation of the Blue Cross''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération Internationale de la Croix-Bleue}}) is a politically and denominationally independent [[Christianity|Christian]] organization consisting of about 40 member organizations engaged in the prevention, treatment and after care of problems related to alcohol and other drugs.
It was founded in 1877 in [[Geneva]] by L-L. Rochat.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Blå Kors|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Bl%C3%A5_Kors|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 July 2009}}</ref>
