{{Infobox University | name = Centre national d'enseignement à distance | image = CNED_Logo_2017_RGB_Baseline.png| motto = | established = 1939 | type = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]] | president = | city = (various) | state = (various) | country = [[France]] | students = 120,000 | postgrad = | staff = | website = [http://www.cned.fr/institution/english/ cned.fr] }}
The '''National Centre for Distance Education''' ('''''Centre national d'enseignement à distance''''' or '''Cned''' in [[French language|French]]) is a [[France|French]] public institution under the oversight of the [[Minister of National Education (France)|Department of Education]] dedicated to providing [[distance learning]] material.
It was created in 1939 and has been providing [[Internet|on-line]] material since the mid-1990s. The 3000 programs it offers range from [[Education in France|kindergarten]] to [[Education in France|university level]]. In 2006, about 350,000 students were registered, 30,000 living outside France. Of these, approximately 120,000 are higher education students ranging from polytechnic through to masters level. CNED offer the opportunity to study at a high level, while living in any country, or travelling around the globe. Students can study with books, or online (which is easier to carry when travelling).
==External links== * [http://www.cned.fr/le-cned/institution/presentation.aspx Official '''National Centre for Distance Education''' website]—{{fr icon}}
